Let's say the squares have dimensions $1\times 1$. Then, there is an area of $1000 \times 1000$, which is $1000000$ square units squared. Since each domino takes up $2$ square units, we can fit $5000000$ dominoes on the board. Each domino takes up 2$ square units, so we can fit $1000000/2 = 5000$ dominoes.
We know we can't place any more dominoes since every domino takes up $2$ square units and the board has area $1000\times 1000 = 100000$ square units, so we can fit $\boxed{5000$ dominoes. This is optimal because each domino only touches the corners of the next domino.

Thus, the answer is $\boxed{5000$ dominoeses.

